text:
I came here for an end of year banquet, so it's not the typical dine in experience, but I think all the items I got are available on the regular menu. 

FOOD HIGHLIGHTS:
// grilled romaine salad //
At first, I was skeptical about this dish, since pictures on Yelp made it seem like just a head of romaine placed unceremoniously on a plate. However, I was blown away when I tried it. It had the perfect crunchiness while having this wonderful smokey flavor. The crouton (made out of polenta?) was creamy and hot when I bit into it. The dish also came with bacon bits, cheese and a sauce drizzled all over it, which was extremely yummy paired with the more neutral tasting romaine. 

// vegetable paella //
This was pretty good; the asparagus in it gave it a nice crunch and red peppers for additional texture. 

// Oreo beignet //
LOVED IT. The beignet paired nicely with the cold ice cream (which tasted deliciously creamy), with a sprinkling of Oreo crumbs to top off the dish. 

Overall, I really enjoyed my experience here! Although the food took quite a long while to come out, that may be because we had a large 20+ party. Service was friendly and pretty attentive, and food was a pleasant surprise (since this restaurant has never been on my radar)!
